WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:10.968
This Core edition shows how to build a new client’s file from source evidence. The model connects

2
00:00:10.968 --> 00:00:21.136
five elements: incoming documents and where they came from; client identity and the people involved; requested services

3
00:00:21.136 --> 00:00:31.724
and engagement facts; open requests with their next actions; and dates and history maintained over time. The elements

4
00:00:31.724 --> 00:00:41.892
remain distinct but connected, so every fact can be traced to the document or decision behind it.

5
00:00:41.892 --> 00:00:52.060
Each country maps its own documents, checks and rules onto this shared structure. The result is a

6
00:00:52.060 --> 00:00:59.200
readable client file that shows what is known, what remains open and how the professional relationship develops.
